item.title: 'Stealth version of the far left': Comedian Bill Maher advises Kamala Harris against posing herself as 'woke President'
item.description: Comedian Bill Maher suggests that Vice President Kamala Harris must convince voters she is not aligned with extreme leftist views to appeal to undecided voters. Maher advises against presenting as a 'woke' candidate, noting the term's evolving meaning. Harris has adjusted her stance on several policies since her 2020 campaign, while maintaining consistent values.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: NYU family weekend: Will there be anyone for Barron Trump?
item.description: New York University is hosting its alumni and family weekend at Washington Square Park, where the family members of the freshman students are likely to turn up. As many celebrity kids attend NYU, the event is likely to become a star-studded affair but it is highly unlikely that Barron Trump's parents will attend the event and Trump is busy in election preparation and Melania with her book events.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: 'Neither Kamala nor Trump...': Pollster predicts election outcome that hasn't happened in 36 years
item.description: GOP pollster Mitchell Brown predicts neither Donald Trump nor Kamala Harris will win all three key battleground states — Michigan, Wisconsin, and Pennsylvania. The race remains tight with a potential Trump victory if he takes one of these states. Analysts are divided, with polls predicting a competitive contest. "What I see here, is that neither candidate would win all three of those, that means Trump just taking one—he has the election won," Brown said on Thursday.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Bizarre! Missouri man lived with 175 cats, daughter was not allowed to enter
item.description: In Missouri's St. Louis County, an elderly man was forced to leave his home after his daughter discovered he was living in squalor with 175 cats. The daughter gained access to the house after her mother passed away, revealing the deplorable conditions. The daughter said a relative came to stay with their parents who blocked everyone's entry to the house and that went on for years.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Donald Trump says he may pardon Hunter Biden because...
item.description: Former President Donald Trump stated in an interview that he would consider pardoning Hunter Biden, the first child of a sitting president to be convicted of a crime. ​"See, unlike Joe Biden, despite what they’ve done to me, where they’ve gone after me so viciously, despite what — and Hunter’s a bad boy. There’s no question about it. He’s been a bad boy. All you had to do is see the laptop from hell. But I happen to think it’s very bad for our country," Trump said.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Kamala Harris book author attacks her faith: 'Vengeful Hindu goddess'
item.description: "I was raised to believe in a loving God, to believe that your faith is a verb, live your faith," Kamala Harris told Anderson Cooper as her faith is a much-discussed issue this election after the Donald Trump campaign called her 'anti-Christ'. Kamala Harris said she prays every day and sometimes twice a day and when President Joe Biden withdrew from the race endorsing her, she called her pastor Reverend Amos C. Brown of the Third Baptist Church of San Francisco.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: 'Witches are trying to cast spells on Trump but can't...' Reddit thread viral
item.description: A report claimed that each month, thousands of American voters who are self-identified witches -- gather online and in person to prevent Donald Trump from winning the election. The anti-Trump "witches" use orange candles for their binding spell that aims to prevent Trump from doing any further harm., the report said.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: After Springsteen and Eminem, Beyonce to perform in Harris's campaign rally
item.description: Pop icon Beyonce will perform at a rally for Vice President Kamala Harris in Houston. Harris is campaigning across the country before the election, focusing on key issues like abortion rights. The event in Texas coincides with a tight Senate race between Sen. Ted Cruz and Rep. Colin Allred.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Abhijit Banerjee among 23 economists who endorsed Kamala Harris over Donald Trump
item.description: Twenty-three Nobel Prize-winning economists endorse Vice President Kamala Harris for the US Presidential elections, citing her policies as offering stronger, more equitable economic growth compared to Trump's proposals, which are viewed as inflationary and deficit-increasing. Notable signatories include Joseph Stiglitz, Daron Acemoglu, and Abhijit Banerjee.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: 'Slaps so hard I spin around': Doug Emhoff's ex-girlfriend speaks out about 2012 assault
item.description: “As I’m talking to him, Doug got out of the line, comes up, turns me around by my right shoulder. I’m completely caught off guard, I’m not bracing, I’m in four-inch heels, wearing a full-length gown and it’s between 2-3 a.m.,” Doug Emhoff's ex-girlfriend told the DailyMail. “He slaps me so hard I spin around, and I’m in utter shock.” Earlier, Doug's office denied the incident.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Elon Musk's dinner with Rupert Murdoch: 'He's doing for Trump what he did for Tesla'
item.description: ​Elon Musk Monday traveled from Pittsburgh to New York for a sinner with Rupert Murdoch and other business leaders to discuss the state of the race, a New York Times report said citing a person with knowledge of the meal. ​"In some ways, what Mr Musk has done for Tesla, the electric car company, is not terribly different from what he is doing now for Mr Trump," the NYT report noted.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Boulevard of ‘brokenist’ dreams: Justin Trudeau’s tryst with parliamentary language
item.description: The term “brokenist” emerged during a heated session in which Justin Trudeau aimed to highlight the alleged negativity and obstructionism of the opposition, particularly the Conservative Party, under its leader Pierre Poilievre. Trudeau’s use of the term seemed to suggest that the opposition was overly focused on portraying Canada as “broken,” a theme Poilievre had used repeatedly in his critique of Trudeau’s government.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Pro-Trump handles trend #KamalaGropedMeToo after Stacey Williams' allegations
item.description: The hashtag #KamalaGropedMeToo, trending among pro-Trump supporters, appears to be a disinformation campaign aimed at deflecting attention from new sexual misconduct allegations against Donald Trump. The trend uses baseless claims targeting Vice President Kamala Harris, attempting to discredit her and shift focus away from Trump’s legal troubles. This strategy exploits social media to spread false narratives, undermining both Harris and the broader #MeToo movement, while highlighting the challenges of combating disinformation in today’s political landscape.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Can't be a coincidence that everyone hates Meghan Markle: Royal expert
item.description: Royal expert Hugo Vickers said Meghan's profile got a raise after marrying Prince Harry but Meghan was never particularly committed to becoming a member of the Royal Family. "It does seem to me that she wasn't particularly committed to being a member of the Royal Family. By marrying Prince Harry, her profile went up globally, enormously, and so people wanted to hear more about her, and to some extent more from her..." Vickers said.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Amid groping allegation, Donald Trump's past comments about daughter Ivanka viral
item.description: ​“You know who’s one of the great beauties of the world, according to everybody? And I helped create her. Ivanka. My daughter, Ivanka. She’s 6 feet tall, she’s got the best body. She made a lot money as a model—a tremendous amount," Trump said in 2003 on the Howard Stern Show. The video went viral as Trump faces a new allegation from former model Stacy Williams that he groped her at a party.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Watch: Tucker Carlson's weird rant, 'Daddy Donald Trump will give spanking'
item.description: Tucker Carlson, speaking at a Georgia rally for Donald Trump, likened Trump's potential victory to a father's return to home to discipline truant kids. Carlson said when Dad Trump comes home, he's pissed but "not vengeful" and "loves his children, disobedient as they may be". The father figure would need to let the child (country) know that he's very disappointed in their behavior.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk
